# Publish & Push Checklist

## Before `npm publish` (CLI package)

Run ALL checks in order. Do not skip any:

```bash
# 1. All component tests must pass
npm test

# 2. CLI-specific tests must pass
cd packages/cli && npm test

# 3. Prefix validation — ensures tw- prefixing is correct
cd packages/cli && npm run validate:prefix

# 4. Full build pipeline
cd packages/cli && npm run build
```

Only proceed with publish if every step above exits with code 0.

```bash
cd packages/cli
npm version patch   # or minor/major
npm publish
```

## Before `git push`

```bash
cd packages/cli && npm run validate:prefix
```

This validates the `tw-` prefix transformation is correct before the code reaches CI.

## After Publishing CLI — Sync the MCP Server

If you added or modified components, update the MCP package:

```bash
# 1. Sync component metadata from components.yaml
node scripts/sync-mcp-metadata.js --write

# 2. Build and publish MCP
cd packages/mcp
npm version patch
npm run build
npm publish
```

**Checklist before finishing any publish task:**
- [ ] `npm test` passes (root)
- [ ] `cd packages/cli && npm test` passes
- [ ] `npm run validate:prefix` passes
- [ ] `npm run build` succeeds
- [ ] CLI version bumped and published
- [ ] MCP metadata synced (`sync-mcp-metadata.js`)
- [ ] MCP version bumped and published
